	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Speaking of what you think you know, very good post on what you think you know.<BR>
Simple fact is you are right in one point. Some people can't file stuff away correctly. Is this just a birth defect? Most likely not. Everyone is different, and that goes for parents and family as well. Most people are the way they are because of their parents influence, or lack thereof. Some are similar to their parents, if they had respect for them and played an active part in their lives. Some are the exact opposite if the parents always had the child play outside, in their room or just be quiet so dad can watch tv. Then, there are some that don't follow these standards, because each person is different and how they turn out depends mostly on their parents involvement and somewhat on what that child wants to be. What the child wants to be depends alot on their parents as well, though.<BR>
If all your life your mother or father talked about how stupid and underpaid firemen were (just an example), and how a fireman is just a dropout with a coat that can use a hose, would you want to become a fireman? Maybe, depending on how much you respected your parents.<BR>
Regardless of what anyone wants to think, parents play the biggest role in life. When my daughter starts going to school I can take confidence in the fact that my raising her and teaching her what I am will help her differentiate between the people she can and should not talk to. It's like telling your child not to talk to strangers. If your child thinks you are intelligent and an actual authority figure, they will listen. If you are a half-wit, your children know that.<BR>
<BR>
Darklyth
				</font>
