	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				You know, i'm reading a lot about how games, music, movies and various other forms of entertainment don't make someone (especially young kids) murder, steal or commit other crimes.<BR>
<BR>
I hate to tell you this but they do contribute to it.<BR>
<BR>
If you think about it most of what you've become and will become is due to outside influences. Whether it be music and movies or your parents and &quot;peer pressure&quot;. The fact of the matter is just about everything you hear and see each day is taken in by your mind, disected and spit back out in some form of thought. You are who you are because of so many things; upbringing, geographic location, social status....and yes, games, movies and music. If this werent the case we would all be the same. We'd be born the same and die the same.<BR>
<BR>
The key here is to take all of that crap that fills your head every second of every day and file it away in the appropriate spot. &quot;That guy just stole my uber loot in this game im playing!&quot;. Personally I'd file that in the &quot;oh well&quot; spot. Apparently this guy filed it away in the &quot;this means all the world to me&quot; spot.<BR>
<BR>
I think someone with &quot;issues&quot; is someone who cant file stuff away in the appropriate spot. What is fantasy is filed away in reality and so on. (no im not smoking anything [yet] so bear with me). Its like some uneducated fool not being able to realize that B comes between A and C so his collection of CDs is in some whacked out alphabetical order.<BR>
<BR>
Which makes me wonder what this guys education was? Hmmm.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway. Just recently I saw a movie most of you have probably heard of; Reservoire Dogs. I had heard how &quot;awesome&quot; this movie was but when I watched it I couldnt believe what i was seeing and hearing (and not much offends me). Aside from the &quot;F word&quot; being spoken about 6 trillion times (and thats no lie) we have a scene where a guy gets his ear cut off while strapped to a chair. Also the &quot;gangsters&quot; are a group of bada$$-im-not-taking-crap-from-you types. I sat there and could actually imagine young kids, after watching this movie, taking that same attitude to school or to work.<BR>
<BR>
And some do.<BR>
<BR>
My point is that to say a game, movie, music etc. cant make someone do something stupid like kill themselves or murder....<BR>
<BR>
is B.S.<BR>
<BR>
Sorry, but that is just the truth. We see it all the time (this article being only one of those times).<BR>
<BR>
Your homework assignment is this; for those of you who disagree I want you to think about all those things you THINK you know. We'll even make it easier for you. We'll take a semi-recent event like Sept 11th. Now, what do you KNOW about Sept. 11th and the events that occured thereafter (the war waging now)? And of all those things you think you KNOW....how many are first-hand experiences.....and how many are those you heard from TV, radio, the paper??<BR>
<BR>
My point is what you know and what you think you know is GREATLY influenced by those very mediums you are trying to say have no effect on you.<BR>
<BR>
Did this kid kill himself because of the game? Who knows. Could the game have contributed to his suicide? You bet. Is SOE then responsible? No. Again, its all about being able to file stuff in the appropriate spot and SOE cant be held responsible if you dont do it correctly.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
