	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				BTW, Zooh Flesheater I think it was? Don't be a prick. Have at least the smallest amount of respect. Ragardless if you are trying to make a comment that would be considered funny in game to your guild, try to keep the garbage to a minimum on the boards.<BR>
One more thing. EQ is addictive if you allow it to be. In the 3 years I've played, I've averaged a break every 6-7 months. Usually for a month and a half at a time. That's usually when I am getting so into the game that I can't remember when the last time I did anything productive was. If I get off work and go straight home and jump on EQ and not log off until bedtime, it's time for a change.<BR>
Best guideline I can suggest to go by... If you play EQ more hours a week than you spend doing any of the following things, it is time to back off of it. The following are:<BR>
A. Watching TV.<BR>
B. Anything done outdoors.<BR>
C. Non-computer activities with family.<BR>
<BR>
Can you remember the last time you did any of those things without struggling not to run to the computer and log in? If every time you sit down away from your computer, all you can think about is what you could do if you logged in, yer a junkie and need to back off for a bit. It's much better when your weekend is spent on EQ only 2 hours a day. The weekend seems so much longer. And the week isn't nearly as bad when you actually log off and sleep a little bit. Otherwise work/school can be utter hell.<BR>
<BR>
Try to be careful and use judgement. If you are called an EQ junkie by people that don't play EQ, odds are they are right. If you talk about EQ to your friends more often than you talk about anything else, put the keyboard down and step away. Lastly, if you can't remember the last fight you had with your significant other that didn't involve you saying, &quot;Sec hon, mob on me.&quot;... Log off for awhile!<BR>
I've lost one girlfriend over EQ and OUR addiction to it. A couple years later, looking back it seems like such a waste. I cannot believe I wasted what could have been a wonderful life with this woman over EQ. Don't end up in those shoes looking back.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Darklyth again.<BR>
Test Server.
				</font>
			</td>

